#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29, sc29
msgctxt "mn12:29.1"
msgid "Aṭṭha kho imā, sāriputta, parisā. "
msgstr "Sāriputta, there are these eight assemblies. "

msgctxt "mn12:29.2"
msgid "Katamā aṭṭha? "
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "mn12:29.3"
msgid "Khattiyaparisā, brāhmaṇaparisā, gahapatiparisā, samaṇaparisā, cātumahārājikaparisā, tāvatiṃsaparisā, māraparisā, brahmaparisā—"
msgstr "The assemblies of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, and ascetics. An assembly of the gods under the Four Great Kings. An assembly of the gods under the Thirty-Three. An assembly of Māras. An assembly of Brahmās. "

msgctxt "mn12:29.4"
msgid "imā kho, sāriputta, aṭṭha parisā. "
msgstr "These are the eight assemblies. "

msgctxt "mn12:29.5"
msgid "Imehi kho, sāriputta, catūhi vesārajjehi samannāgato tathāgato imā aṭṭha parisā upasaṅkamati ajjhogāhati. "
msgstr "Possessing these four kinds of self-assurance, the Realized One approaches and enters right into these eight assemblies. "

# NOTE: BB has “many hundreds of assemblies” but at AN 8.69 he changes it to “an assembly consisting of many hundreds”
msgctxt "mn12:29.6"
msgid "Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, anekasataṃ khattiyaparisaṃ upasaṅkamitā. "
msgstr "I recall having approached an assembly of hundreds of aristocrats. "

msgctxt "mn12:29.7"
msgid "Tatrapi mayā sannisinnapubbañceva, sallapitapubbañca, sākacchā ca samāpajjitapubbā. "
msgstr "There I used to sit with them, converse, and engage in discussion. "

msgctxt "mn12:29.8"
msgid "Tatra vata maṃ bhayaṃ vā sārajjaṃ vā okkamissatīti nimittametaṃ, sāriputta, na samanupassāmi. "
msgstr "But I don’t see any reason to feel afraid or insecure. "

msgctxt "mn12:29.9"
msgid "Etamahaṃ, sāriputta, nimittaṃ asamanupassanto khemappatto abhayappatto vesārajjappatto viharāmi. "
msgstr "Since I see no such reason, I live secure, fearless, and assured. "

