#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya35, pts-vp-pli1.74, sc34
msgctxt "mn12:35.1"
msgid "Pañca kho imā, sāriputta, gatiyo. "
msgstr "There are these five destinations. "

msgctxt "mn12:35.2"
msgid "Katamā pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "mn12:35.3"
msgid "Nirayo, tiracchānayoni, pettivisayo, manussā, devā. "
msgstr "Hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, humanity, and the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya36
msgctxt "mn12:36.1"
msgid "Nirayañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, nirayagāmiñca maggaṃ, nirayagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; "
msgstr "I understand hell, and the path and practice that leads to hell. "

msgctxt "mn12:36.2"
msgid "yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr "And I understand how someone practicing that way, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "mn12:36.3"
msgid "Tiracchānayoniñcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, tiracchānayonigāmiñca maggaṃ, tiracchānayonigāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; "
msgstr "I understand the animal realm … "

msgctxt "mn12:36.4"
msgid "yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn12:36.5"
msgid "Pettivisayañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, pettivisayagāmiñca maggaṃ, pettivisayagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn12:36.6"
msgid "yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr "the ghost realm … "

msgctxt "mn12:36.7"
msgid "Manusse cāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, manussalokagāmiñca maggaṃ, manussalokagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; "
msgstr "humanity … "

msgctxt "mn12:36.8"
msgid "yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjati tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn12:36.9"
msgid "Deve cāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, devalokagāmiñca maggaṃ, devalokagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; "
msgstr "gods, and the path and practice that leads to the world of the gods. "

msgctxt "mn12:36.10"
msgid "yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr "And I understand how someone practicing that way, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "mn12:36.11"
msgid "Nibbānañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, nibbānagāmiñca maggaṃ, nibbānagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; "
msgstr "And I understand extinguishment, and the path and practice that leads to extinguishment. "

msgctxt "mn12:36.12"
msgid "yathā paṭipanno ca āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr "And I understand how someone practicing that way realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya37, sc35
msgctxt "mn12:37.1"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand: "

msgctxt "mn12:37.2"
msgid "tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatīti. "
msgstr "‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’ "

msgctxt "mn12:37.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. "
msgstr "Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in hell, where they experience exclusively painful feelings, sharp and severe. "

msgctxt "mn12:37.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā pūrā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ vītadhūmānaṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, full of glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked. "

msgctxt "mn12:37.5"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva aṅgārakāsuṃ paṇidhāya. "
msgstr "Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same pit of coals. "

msgctxt "mn12:37.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say: "

msgctxt "mn12:37.7"
msgid "‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā imaṃyeva aṅgārakāsuṃ āgamissatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very pit of coals.’ "

msgctxt "mn12:37.8"
msgid "Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tassā aṅgārakāsuyā patitaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. "
msgstr "Then some time later they see that they have indeed fallen into that pit of coals, where they experience exclusively painful feelings, sharp and severe. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn12:37.9"
msgid "Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr " "

